WEBVTT

00:00.151 --> 00:01.770
What can I do for you?

00:02.713 --> 00:06.967
Well I'm calling to book a table for four people,...

00:07.585 --> 00:10.384
...and also I'd like to ask you a few questions.

00:10.912 --> 00:13.852
Certainly, sir. What do you need to know?

00:14.852 --> 00:17.589
Well, what are your opening hours?

00:18.413 --> 00:22.326
Our restaurant is open from Tuesday to Sunday.

00:22.721 --> 00:23.910
We're closed on Mondays.

00:25.096 --> 00:27.139
And is there a car park?

00:27.386 --> 00:30.803
Yes, the car park is at the back of the restaurant.

00:31.902 --> 00:34.938
Great, and what time do you serve lunch?

00:35.243 --> 00:38.661
We serve lunch from 12:00 to 2:30.

00:39.401 --> 00:41.147
From 12:00 to 2:30.

00:42.148 --> 00:44.759
Well, then I'd like to make a reservation then.

00:45.464 --> 00:46.963
Certainly sir. When for?

00:48.072 --> 00:49.521
For this coming Sunday.

00:51.317 --> 00:53.311
Lunchtime or evening?

00:53.599 --> 00:57.512
For lunch. We'll be coming around 1 o'clock.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.685
One o'clock. OK.

01:00.848 --> 01:02.077
For how many people?

01:02.595 --> 01:03.374
For four.

01:04.066 --> 01:05.033
Very well, sir.

01:05.317 --> 01:07.218
What's the name please?

01:07.549 --> 01:08.247
Monaghan.

01:08.933 --> 01:10.230
Could you spell that, please?

01:10.334 --> 01:19.881
Yeah. M O N A G H A N.

01:21.157 --> 01:27.094
Alright Mr. Monaghan, one table for four for Sunday, 1:00 p.m.

01:27.413 --> 01:29.118
Yeah, that's great.

